FROM THE ARCHIVES: AMAZING cover star @andreariseborough  has been nominated for an Oscar for her leading role in “To Leslie.” Riseborough made the bold move to carry out a grassroots social media campaign to boost the film’s visibility. While many have said her Best Actress nomination is a controversial, another perspective can point to her unwavering ethos of receiving the recognition deserved for her years work as a reputable female actress. 

AMAZING Editor-at-Large, J.L. Sirisuk (@the_zenjendaya ) spoke with Riseborough about her work in ‘To Leslie’ in Issue N°14: 

“The woman whose life this is based on, this piece was
penned by her son [Ryan Binaco], Riseborough told Sirisuk. “She sadly passed away. My perspective on this piece has always been on the retelling of this story by screenwriter Ryan [Binaco] and wanting to focus on this piece as he gave his mother the ending she may not have been
able to have in her life. He didn’t shy away from exploring how challenging she finds it just to live. At the same time, it gives her the opportunity at the end for reconnection. That’s what he needed to do, to say goodbye to her. He needed to give her a better ending...Ryan has reset the story, there are many parallels that are not set in stone, so in a sense on one hand we were creating from scratch because Ryan retold the story in
Texas, which is not where it really happened. As much as Leslie
was there, we were building a new person who lived in a different
part of America. Very little discussion about that was my work. [read in caption for rest].
